Only visited the Aqua Park. A good day out with the kids. You can use the hotel pool for a bit of peace and quiet or use the wave pool and slides.There are plenty of slides etc for young kids also
We had a meeting with the governors, in the conference hall. It was a great atmosphere. Thanks to the hotel.

I spent a few days in Spring here.  Reception and staff were very helpful and attentive. The room service food was very good.  Breakfast had many choices.  Liked the small balcony and view of Caspian Sea. Told them to replace the weight machine in fitness room.  It was not very easy to use.  They held special events, but I did not hear it from my room. I would return and stay again.
Small hotel at the great location. The room is big enough. Very good swimming pool that was open in December with comfortable changing room. Good sauna.
Very nice hotel with sea view and comfortable & fairly new rooms. There is an aquapark that can be fun to use in summer time.

The pool is crowded and they take turns at the entrance. The name is read to enter the pool. Think of it like the old hospital system in Turkey. So, we are tired of having fun and people are entering the pool with their clothes on. I give both points for the people trying to take care of us.

The staff are lovely, helpful and very attentive. The hotel is clean, tidy and very pleasant spaces. Breakfast was very nice and plentiful. Our room had a balcony with sea view that was lovely but also view to the water park, thankfully there was nobody there as it would be noisy. The spa area is very pleasant with a lovely swimming pool and sauna. You have to tell them one hour before if you want to use the sauna as it's kept off. The service and eye for detail can improve for example there was no toilet paper in our room and there was only one bathrope but two one litre bottles of water were very welcomed. I recommend it and hope to be back.
